name: AdjuvantPainMedications
title: Adjuvant pain medications
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: Medicine which has a primary indication other than pain, but is analgesic in some painful conditions.),(Data Element Scope: FHIR MedicationRequest and MedicationStatement),(Inclusion Criteria: RXNORM codes derived from the following: descendants of “Pain may treat” in The Medication Reference Terminology (MED-RT); “Anti-inflammatory and Antirheumatic Products” in the Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) Classification System; “Analgesics, Non-Narcotic” in the National Library of Medicine Medical Subject Headings (MeSH); “Analgesics”.
Include medications that have a primary indication for a "non-pain" condition (e.g., SNRIs for depression) but used with other pain meds.),(Exclusion Criteria: Opioid medications, non-opioid medications indicated for acute pain.  Excludes medicines administered primarily to manage adverse effects associated with analgesics, such as laxatives and anti-emetics.)
